rComments: He lectures very hard but tests easy (if you spent the time studying). Some people find his lectures too difficult because he uses lots of proofs but I really love how explains how everything works instead of just giving you something to memorize. He is super smart and you can tell his passion for math.
He's a great professor, but keep in mind MAT137 is one of the hardest math courses offered!   He's friendly, responsible, well organized, not to mention really smart!

He's the politest and nicest calculus prof you'll have. He's very intelligent and know almost anything that you ask him without sounding cocky. He is very innocent but has some funny humour. Tests are fairly easy too.
